### =============================================================================
###  Kingdom backend — manual API tests  (IntelliJ HTTP Client)
###
###  HOW TO RUN:
###    1) Start the app  (green Run button in IntelliJ, or:  mvn spring-boot:run)
###    2) Click the green ▶ arrow to the LEFT of any "###" request below
###    3) The response (status + body) opens in the Services/Run panel
###
###  STATUS CODES you will see (you already met all of these with Neotek!):
###    200 OK            -> success
###    400 Bad Request   -> your body is missing/!invalid (validation)
###    401 Unauthorized  -> missing/!wrong token
###    403 Forbidden     -> no access / not subscribed
###    404 Not Found     -> wrong URL, or the id doesn't exist
###    500 Server Error  -> the server code threw an exception
### =============================================================================

@base = http://localhost:8080/api/v1

### 1. List all challenges   (expect 200 + a JSON array; [] if none yet)
GET {{base}}/challenge/get
Accept: application/json

### 2. Get one challenge by id   (404 if it doesn't exist)
GET {{base}}/challenge/get/1
Accept: application/json

### 3. Add a challenge   (NOTE: no xpReward — the server fills it from the fixed table)
POST {{base}}/challenge/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Walk 8000 steps",
  "description": "Reach 8000 steps today (tracked by Google Health).",
  "period": "DAILY",
  "difficulty": "EASY",
  "verificationSource": "GOOGLE_HEALTH",
  "metricKey": "steps",
  "targetValue": 8000,
  "kingdomId": 1
}

### 4. Add a BAD challenge (missing title) -> should return 400 with a validation message.
###    This is how you PROVE your @Valid rules work.
POST {{base}}/challenge/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "no title on purpose",
  "period": "DAILY",
  "difficulty": "EASY",
  "verificationSource": "GOOGLE_HEALTH"
}

### 5. Browse active challenges by difficulty
GET {{base}}/challenge/difficulty/EASY
Accept: application/json

### 6. Join a challenge: player 1 joins challenge 1
###    (needs a Player + a KingdomMembership + the challenge to already exist —
###     use your teammate's demo data, or create them first, else you'll get an error)
POST {{base}}/challenge-progress/join/1/1

### 7. See player 1's active challenges
GET {{base}}/challenge-progress/player/1/active
Accept: application/json

### 8. Finish a run (id 1) -> awards XP + recomputes division + bumps the daily streak
POST {{base}}/challenge-progress/finish/1


### =============================================================================
###  Neotek (Open Banking) — these go STRAIGHT to Neotek's sandbox, server-to-server,
###  so there is NO CORS error like the browser "Try It" gives you.
###
###  FIRST: open  http-client.private.env.json  (next to this file), paste your real
###  client id/secret, then pick the "dev" environment (top-right of this editor).
### =============================================================================

### N1. Get a Neotek token  (saves the access_token so request N2 can reuse it)
POST https://test.api.neotek.sa/oauth2security/oauth2/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=client_credentials&client_id={{neotekClientId}}&client_secret={{neotekClientSecret}}&scope=single_api

> {%
    client.global.set("neotekToken", response.body.access_token);
    client.test("Token returned 200", function () {
        client.assert(response.status === 200, "status was " + response.status);
    });
%}

### N2. List banks   (uses the token captured in N1)
GET https://test.api.neotek.sa/financial-institutions-information/v1/financial-institutions
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{neotekToken}}

### N3. Get an OB-CONNECT token   (creating a consent link needs scope ob_connect, NOT single_api)
POST https://test.api.neotek.sa/oauth2security/oauth2/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=client_credentials&client_id={{neotekClientId}}&client_secret={{neotekClientSecret}}&scope=ob_connect

> {%
    client.global.set("neotekConnectToken", response.body.access_token);
%}

### N4. Create Accounts Link (consent)  ==> WORKS with bank SAIBCSARI (Saib / Saudi Investment Bank).
###     Returns 201 + Data.AccountsLinkId + Data.RedirectionURL. Open that RedirectionURL in a browser,
###     log into the sandbox mock bank, and approve -> that activates the consent for this PSUId.
###     (The earlier 500 was just the wrong bank: BSFR/INMA/SAMAModelBank aren't provisioned for consent.)
POST https://test.api.neotek.sa/accounts-information/v1/accounts-links
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{neotekConnectToken}}

{
  "Data": {
    "FinancialInstitutionId": "SAIBCSARI",
    "SecurityProfile": "Redirection",
    "DataGroups": [
      { "DataGroupId": "AccountDetails", "Permissions": ["ReadAccountsBasic", "ReadAccountsDetail"] },
      { "DataGroupId": "AccountTransactions", "Permissions": ["ReadTransactionsBasic", "ReadTransactionsDetail", "ReadTransactionsDebits"] }
    ],
    "PSUId": "20112"
  }
}


### =============================================================================
###  Strava (Fitness) — REAL activity data. ONE-TIME setup to get a refresh token:
###    1) register an app at  https://www.strava.com/settings/api  (Callback Domain = localhost)
###    2) open this in your BROWSER (replace YOUR_CLIENT_ID), then click Authorize:
###       https://www.strava.com/oauth/authorize?client_id=YOUR_CLIENT_ID&response_type=code&redirect_uri=http://localhost/exchange_token&approval_prompt=force&scope=activity:read_all
###    3) the browser fails to load localhost — that's fine; copy the  code=...  value from the address bar
###    4) paste it into S0 below, run S0 ONCE -> copy "refresh_token" from the response
###    5) put client id/secret + that refresh_token into http-client.private.env.json (and application-local.properties)
### =============================================================================

### S0. ONE-TIME: exchange the authorize "code" for tokens   (replace PASTE_CODE_HERE)
POST https://www.strava.com/api/v3/oauth/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

client_id={{stravaClientId}}&client_secret={{stravaClientSecret}}&code=PASTE_CODE_HERE&grant_type=authorization_code

### S1. Refresh -> access token   (run this each time; Strava tokens last 6 hours)
POST https://www.strava.com/api/v3/oauth/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

client_id={{stravaClientId}}&client_secret={{stravaClientSecret}}&grant_type=refresh_token&refresh_token={{stravaRefreshToken}}

> {%
    client.global.set("stravaToken", response.body.access_token);
%}

### S2. List my recent activities   (uses the token captured in S1)
GET https://www.strava.com/api/v3/athlete/activities?per_page=10
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{stravaToken}}


### =============================================================================
###  VERIFICATION FLOW (YOUR backend) — RESTART your app first so it has these endpoints.
###  Needs neotek.enabled=true + strava.enabled=true in application-local.properties.
###  Charity reads Neotek (real sandbox); Fitness reads Strava (real account).
### =============================================================================

### V1. Charity — start a consent (returns AccountsLinkId + RedirectionURL; open the URL in a browser + approve)
POST {{base}}/verify/charity/link?psuId=20112

### V2. Charity — inspect the consented account's transactions
GET {{base}}/verify/charity/transactions?psuId=20112
Accept: application/json

### V3. Charity — PASS RULE: any outgoing booked donation >= 1 SAR (window = last 10 years)
GET {{base}}/verify/charity/check?psuId=20112&minAmountSar=1&fromDays=3650
Accept: application/json

### V4. Charity — PASS RULE for a named charity (>= 100 SAR whose payee/narrative contains "Ehsan")
GET {{base}}/verify/charity/check?psuId=20112&minAmountSar=100&charityName=Ehsan&fromDays=3650
Accept: application/json

### V5. Fitness — list my Strava activities
GET {{base}}/verify/fitness/activities?fromDays=30
Accept: application/json

### V6. Fitness — PASS RULE: did I cover >= 5000 m of running this month?
GET {{base}}/verify/fitness/check?metricKey=distance_meters&targetValue=5000&sportType=Run&fromDays=30
Accept: application/json

### V7. Volunteer — upload a certificate PDF for AI verification
###     Put a file named certificate.pdf next to this file first (or change the path after the "<").
###     Needs openai.enabled=true + a real openai.api-key in application-local.properties.
POST {{base}}/verify/volunteer/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=KingdomBoundary

--KingdomBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="activity"

beach cleanup
--KingdomBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="certificate.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./certificate.pdf
--KingdomBoundary--
